Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{20-30%seconds}.

> For 4 servings: Use 4 TBSP butter.

Pour @marinara{14%oz} into a #large bowl{}. Stir in @gnocchi{8.8%oz}, half the melted butter (you'll use the rest in the next step), @water{1/2%cup}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and a pinch of @chilies flakes{pinch} to taste until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings: Use 1 cup water.

Divide gnocchi mixture between #oven-ready aluminum trays{2}.

Stir @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} into bowl with remaining melted butter.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; drizzle with @olive oil{some}. Season all over with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place one cutlet in each #tray{} on top of gnocchi mixture.

Sprinkle panko mixture evenly over each chicken cutlet. Bake on top rack until chicken is cooked through and topping is golden brown, ~{22-25%minutes}.

Let cool at least ~{5%minutes}, then divide between plates and top with more @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Serve.

> TIP: If you prefer a more deeply brown crust, broil for an additional 2-3 minutes (just be sure to watch carefully to avoid burning).